<a href="http://www.npr.org/2013/02/25/172900833/do-we-need-humans" target="_blank"><img alt='TRH: Robots' class='Figure__image' src='//pb-assets.tedcdn.com/system/baubles/files/000/000/984/original/topics_TRH_robots.jpg?1401475770'>
</a></figure>
<div class='copy text-left'>
<h4 class="h7 m5">Episode: Do We Need Humans?</h4>

<p>We’ve been promised a future where robots will be our friends, and technology will make life’s daily chores as easy as flipping a switch. But are we ready for how those innovations will change us as humans? In this episode, TED speakers consider the promises and perils of our relationship with technology. <a href="http://www.npr.org/2013/02/25/172900833/do-we-need-humans"><strong>Listen now</strong></a></p>

